Package com.qdc.lims.entity

package com.qdc.lims.entity
JPA entity model representing the domain and persistence schema.

Entities define the core business concepts such as patients, orders, tests, inventory, and financial ledgers.

    Description
    com.qdc.lims
    LIMS application root package.

    Class
    Description
    CommissionLedger
    Entity representing a commission ledger entry for a lab order and doctor.
    Department
    Department (also used as a "category" in the UI) that groups related TestDefinition and Panel entries.
    Doctor
    Entity representing a doctor and their commission details.
    InventoryItem
    Entity representing an inventory item and its stock details.
    LabInfo
    Entity representing laboratory information and contact details.
    LabOrder
    Entity representing a laboratory order, including patient, doctor, billing, and result details.
    LabResult
    Entity representing a laboratory test result, including value, abnormality, remarks, and audit trail.
    Panel
    A billable panel that groups multiple TestDefinition items under a single name.
    Patient
    Entity representing a patient, including demographic and registration details.
    Payment
    Entity representing a general financial payment or expense.
    Permission
    Entity representing a granular permission (e.g., PATIENT_CREATE, TEST_APPROVE).
    ReferenceRange
    Entity representing age and gender-specific reference ranges for lab test results.
    Role
    Entity representing a user role (e.g., ADMIN, RECEPTIONIST, LAB_TECHNICIAN).
    Supplier
    Entity representing a supplier from whom inventory items are purchased.
    SupplierLedger
    Entity representing a financial ledger entry for tracking purchases from and payments to suppliers.
    SystemConfiguration
    Key-value system configuration entry used by the desktop settings screen.
    TestCategory
    Legacy/alternate test category entity.
    TestConsumption
    Entity representing a recipe that links a test to inventory items and their required quantities.
    TestDefinition
    Master data definition for a laboratory test, including pricing, reference-range metadata, and relationships to departments and panels.
    TestRecipe
    Represents the consumption recipe for a test.
    User
    Entity representing a system user with authentication credentials and role-based access.
